    "body": "## Summary\nFix critical severity security issue in `src/ipc/capnp/common-types.h`.\n\n## Vulnerability\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **ID** | V-001 |\n| **Severity** | CRITICAL |\n| **Scanner** | multi_agent_ai |\n| **Rule** | `V-001` |\n| **File** | `src/ipc/capnp/common-types.h:75` |\n\n**Description**: Multiple memcpy operations in IPC serialization code copy data from source buffers to destination buffers without validating that the destination has sufficient capacity. The code assumes result.begin() points to a buffer large enough to hold stream.size() or str.size() bytes, but there is no explicit validation that result.capacity() >= source.size(). If an attacker can control the size of the source data through crafted IPC messages, they can write beyond the allocated destination buffer boundaries.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/ipc/capnp/common-types.h`\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Build not verified\n- [ ] Scanner re-scan not performed\n- [ ] LLM code review not performed\n\n---\n*Automated security fix by [OrbisAI Security](https://orbisappsec.com)*\n",
